Salihu Lukman, the Director-General of Progressive Governors’ Forum (PGF), has insisted that there is no crisis within the ranks of the All Progressives Congress, APC, governors, despite the current crisis rocking the party. Lukman was reacting to reports of division between governors of the forum. In a statement he signed, Lukman described the reports as false, stressing that the forum was united. He urged Nigerians to disregard the reports. The DG stated that governors are committed to APC both individually and collectively, NAN reports. “In the context of the current challenges facing the party leadership, progressive governors are all working for the quick resolutions of the crisis. “Although approaches and perspectives of each progressive governor may vary, they have been able to debate and reach some consensus on the problems affecting the party as contained in the resolutions of the emergency teleconference meeting of June 13, 2020,” he said.